name: Paraguana Colors #7
description:
Venezuelan photographers always have said that Paraguana is our New York City, I was skeptic because I've never been in NYC but I know the importance of that city for the global community of photographers... So these are my photograhs concerning that first visit to that magic place, because that's what you find in Paraguaná: magic light and magic colors. 
The ruins of "Radio Voz de Venezuela" takes us to the face of a future that never came true, this ambitious project never came to fruition and it's a totem to the excesses of the Saudí Venezuela and the failure of the Venezuelan modernization project.
